--------------------------------------------------------------------------
WHY CC BY-NC 4.0?
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

The Mapping Memory, Mapping Meals archive documents the endangered food
culture and culinary heritage of West Bengal's indigenous communities.
This is a non-commercial, non-funded academic initiative. The
NonCommercial restriction ensures that:

  (1) The indigenous cultural knowledge preserved here is not
      commercially exploited without the consent of source communities.

  (2) The archive remains freely accessible for education, research,
      and community use in perpetuity.

  (3) Commercial food enterprises, publishers, and media organisations
      must seek explicit written consent before using this material
      commercially.

--------------------------------------------------------------------------
ADDITIONAL DATA SHIELD NOTICE — INDIGENOUS DATA SOVEREIGNTY
--------------------------------------------------------------------------

Notwithstanding the CC BY-NC 4.0 licence above, the following
additional restriction applies as a condition of access:

  NON-EXTRACTIVE AI CLAUSE: Corporate and commercial AI systems are
  explicitly PROHIBITED from scraping, harvesting, or otherwise
  ingesting the indigenous knowledge contained in this archive for
  the purpose of training Large Language Models (LLMs), foundation
  models, or any other machine learning systems, without the explicit
  prior consent of the source communities and the project maintainers.

  Entries marked as sacred or restricted are held in a non-public
  layer pending community consultation and are NOT covered by the
  CC BY-NC 4.0 licence.

This restriction represents a commitment to Indigenous data sovereignty
and the prevention of computational colonialism.

For permissions beyond this licence, contact:
mappingmemory.contact@gmail.com

